# Implementation Plan - NotebookLM Automation

We will implement an automated "Sync" script using the unofficial `notebooklm-py` library. This allows us to programmatically list and download notebooks and sources.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Authentication**: You will need to extract your Google Cookies (specifically `__Secure-1PSID` etc.) and place them in [.env.local](file:///c:/Users/daria/.gemini/AXON/workspaces/Proyecto%20MENISCO/dashboard-v3/.env.local). This is necessary because there is no official API.
> **Stability**: This relies on an unofficial library/API which may break if Google changes their backend.

## Proposed Changes

### Configuration
#### [MODIFY] [.env.local](file:///c:/Users/daria/.gemini/AXON/workspaces/Proyecto%20MENISCO/dashboard-v3/.env.local)
- Add `GOOGLE_TOKEN` / `GOOGLE_COOKIES` variable.

### Scripts
#### [NEW] [scripts/sync_notebooklm.py](file:///c:/Users/daria/.gemini/AXON/workspaces/Proyecto%20MENISCO/dashboard-v3/scripts/sync_notebooklm.py)
- Python script to:
    1. Authenticate using cookies.
    2. List all Notebooks.
    3. Download "Audio Overviews" and "Source Texts" to `notebooklm/exports/`.

### Dependencies
- `pip install notebooklm-py` (or add to `requirements.txt` if we had one).

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
1.  **Install**: Run `pip install notebooklm-py` (User/Agent).
2.  **Config**: User adds cookies to [.env.local](file:///c:/Users/daria/.gemini/AXON/workspaces/Proyecto%20MENISCO/dashboard-v3/.env.local).
3.  **Run**: Execute `python scripts/sync_notebooklm.py`.
4.  **Check**: Verify files appear in `notebooklm/exports/`.
